-language discussion of the BOJ's operating procedures and policymaker's views about how BOJ actions affect the Japanese business cycle. Chapter three explores the impact of the BOJ's distinctive window guidance policy on corporate investment, while chapter four looks at how monetary policy affects the term structure of interest rates in Japan. The final two chapters examine the overall effect of monetary policy on real aggregate economic activity. This volume will prove invaluable not only to economists interested in the technical operating procedures of the BOJ, but also to those interested in the Japanese economy and in the operation and outcome of monetary reform in general.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aEconomic policy. 0aMonetary policy -- Japan -- Congresses. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / General.2bisacsh  abank of japan, economic growth, financial market liberalization, money-market transactions, regulation, commercial banks, financing, corporate investments, economics, business cycles, window guidance policy, interest rates, monetary reform, nonfiction, international, foreign, investment, transmission mechanism, term structure, lending, aggregate, supply demand.1 aCampbell, John Y., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHamao, Yasushi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHoshi, Takeo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOkina, Kunio, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aScharfstein, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSingleton, Kenneth J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSingleton, Kenneth J., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aWest, Kenneth D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.